{"data":{"doc":{"editUrl":"https://github.com/JoinColony/colonyNetwork/edit/develop/docs/_TLDR_DomainsSkills.md","frontmatter":{"title":"Domains and Skills"},"htmlAst":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Domains and Skills are concepts that define a colony's organizational structure in a decentralized context, and allow for the division of labor without a strict management hierarchy."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Domains are a structure for compartmentalizing the work and shared resources of a colony into smaller, more specialized sub-groups which are analogous to the departments of a traditional company."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Skills are a similar structure that categorize the "},{"type":"element","tagName":"em","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"type"}]},{"type":"text","value":" of work done, independent of the domain or colony in which the work took place."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"ul","properties":{"className":["md-toc"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#domains"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Domains"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#skills"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Skills"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"li","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#disputes"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Disputes"}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"domains"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#domains","ariaLabel":"domains permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Domains"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Like a file system that contains files and sub-folders, any domain can contain tasks, sub-domains, or both."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"img","properties":{"src":"img/domains_1.png","alt":"Example Domains"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"With the exception of the top-level colony domain, which contains all tasks and sub-domains, every domain in a colony belongs to a larger parent domain."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Every domain has an associated "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonynetwork/whitepaper-tldr-pots-and-funding/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"pot"}]},{"type":"text","value":" which can receive funding (in most circumstances from the parent domain's pot)."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tasks are tagged with a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"DomainId"}]},{"type":"text","value":" that specifies which domain they belong to. When a member of a colony earns internal tokens as a result of a completed task (Managers, Workers, and Evaluators all earn reputation from task completion), they earn reputation in that domain as well as all parent domains, including the colony-wide domain. They do not earn any reputation in child domains."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A well-organized domain hierarchy is one way to isolate and compartmentalize work within a colony: In the Colony Protocol, reputation mediates the flow of funding from parent domains to their children (see "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonynetwork/whitepaper-tldr-pots-and-funding/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"pots"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for more about funding), which may in turn direct funding toward smaller and more specialized or specific child domains or tasks. In version 1 of the colonyNetwork, however, the flow of funds between domain pots is permissioned based on "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonyjs/topics-managing-permissions/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"authority roles"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"skills"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#skills","ariaLabel":"skills permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Skills"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Skills do not exist within a particular colony, but instead are a single structure available to all colonies on the network. The global skill hierarchy is maintained by "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonynetwork/whitepaper-tldr-the-meta-colony-and-clny/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Meta Colony"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Tasks are tagged with a "},{"type":"element","tagName":"code","properties":{"className":["language-text"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"SkillId"}]},{"type":"text","value":" that specifies a skill from the global skill hierarchy. When a member of a colony earns internal tokens for completing a task, they earn reputation in the skill, as well as all parent skills. They do not earn any reputation in child skills."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Even though the global set of Skills is shared by all colonies, reputation earned in a particular skill only affects an individual's influence over the colony in which the reputation was earned."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Skill tags are meant to provide a more fine-grained categorization of work than domains, allowing for tasks within the same domain to be further differentiated."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"See the colonyJS "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonyjs/api-colonyclient/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"colonyClient API"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for implementation details."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"disputes"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#disputes","ariaLabel":"disputes permalink","className":["md-heading-link"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"ariaHidden":"true","focusable":"false","height":"16","version":"1.1","viewBox":"0 0 16 16","width":"16"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"fillRule":"evenodd","d":"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z"},"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Disputes"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Domains and Skills determine the scope of voting in the event of a dispute or collective decision."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In Colony you cannot escalate a decision to higher management, you can only escalate to bigger groups of your peers. Domains and Skills mediate this behavior."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"When an objection is raised, the objector must specify at least one domain or skill which should vote on the issue in the event of a dispute. All members within the specified domain/skill will then carry out a reputation-weighted vote to settle the dispute. If the results of the vote are disagreeable to a sufficient amount of collective reputation, the dispute may be escalated to a parent domain and/or skill with a subsequent round of objection/dispute."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Because of the recursively-awarded reputation in parent domains/skills, an individual will always have the same absolute voting power as a dispute is escalated, but of course will have diminishing proportional voting power as the dispute involves more and more participants."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"See "},{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/colonynetwork/whitepaper-tldr-objections-and-disputes/"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Objections and Disputes"}]},{"type":"text","value":" for more information about the complete dispute resolution process as described in the Colony whitepaper."}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}}},"project":{"slug":"colonynetwork","name":"colonyNetwork","logo":"img/colonyNetwork_color.svg","logoSmall":"img/logomark_colonyNetwork_blue.svg","repoUrl":"https://github.com/JoinColony/colonyNetwork","sectionOrder":["intro","docs","bug-bounty-program","whitepaper-tldr","interface"],"sectionTranslations":null,"sections":[{"name":"Docs","slug":"docs","docs":[{"slug":"extensions","fields":{"locale":"en","slug":"/colonynetwork/docs-extensions"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Extensions","order":5,"section":"Docs"}},{"slug":"get-started","fields":{"locale":"en","slug":"/colonynetwork/docs-get-started"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Get Started","order":7,"section":"Docs"}},{"slug":"overview","fields":{"locale":"en","slug":"/colonynetwork/docs-overview"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Overview","order":1,"section":"Docs"}},{"slug":"modular-permissions","fields":{"locale":"en","slug":"/colonynetwork/docs-modular-permissions"},"frontmatte